#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:644
#, no-c-format
msgid "Highlight Detection Rules"
msgstr "Règles de détection de la coloration syntaxique"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:646
#, no-c-format
msgid "This section describes the syntax detection rules."
msgstr "Cette section décrit les règles de détection syntaxique."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:648
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each rule can match zero or more characters at the beginning of the string "
"they are tested against. If the rule matches, the matching characters are "
"assigned the style or <emphasis>attribute</emphasis> defined by the rule, "
"and a rule may ask that the current context is switched."
msgstr ""
"Chaque règle peut correspondre à zéro ou plusieurs caractères au début de la "
"chaine par rapport à laquelle ils sont testés. Si la règle correspond, les "
"caractères concordants sont affectés au style ou à l'<emphasis>attribut</"
"emphasis> défini par la règle et une règle peut demander que le contexte "
"actuel soit commuté."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:654
#, no-c-format
msgid "A rule looks like this:"
msgstr "Voici à quoi une règle ressemble :"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:656
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;RuleName attribute=&quot;(identifier)&quot; context=&quot;"
"(identifier)&quot; [rule specific attributes] /&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;RuleName attribute=&quot;(identifier)&quot; context=&quot;"
"(identifier)&quot; [attributs propres à la règle] /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:658
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <emphasis>attribute</emphasis> identifies the style to use for matched "
"characters by name, and the <emphasis>context</emphasis> identifies the "
"context to use from here."
msgstr ""
"L'<emphasis>attribut</emphasis> identifie le style à utiliser pour les "
"caractères correspondants par nom, et le <emphasis>contexte</emphasis> "
"identifie le contexte à utiliser à partir de cet endroit."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:662
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <emphasis>context</emphasis> can be identified by:"
msgstr "Le <emphasis>contexte</emphasis> peut être identifié par :"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:666
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An <emphasis>identifier</emphasis>, which is the name of the other context."
msgstr ""
"Un <emphasis>identifiant</emphasis>, qui est le nom de l'autre contexte."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:670
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "An <emphasis>order</emphasis> telling the engine to stay in the current "
#| "context (<userinput>#stay</userinput>), or to pop back to a previous "
#| "context used in the string (<userinput>#pop</userinput>)."
msgid ""
"An <emphasis>order</emphasis> telling the engine to stay in the current "
"context (<userinput>#stay</userinput>), or to pop back to a previous context "
"used in the string (<userinput>#pop</userinput>). An empty or absent context "
"is equivalent to <userinput>#stay</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Un <emphasis>ordre</emphasis> demandant au moteur de rester dans le contexte "
"actuel (<userinput>#stay</userinput>) ou de revenir à un contexte "
"précédemment utilisé dans la chaîne (<userinput>#pop</userinput>)."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:674
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To go back more steps, the #pop keyword can be repeated: "
"<userinput>#pop#pop#pop</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Pour reculer de plusieurs étapes, le mot clé #pop peut être répété : "
"<userinput>#pop#pop#pop</userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:678
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "An <emphasis>order</emphasis> followed by an exclamation mark (<emphasis>!"
#| "</emphasis>) and an <emphasis>identifier</emphasis>, which will make the "
#| "engine first follow the order and then switch to the other context, e.g. "
#| "<userinput>#pop#pop!OtherContext</userinput>."
msgid ""
"An <emphasis>order</emphasis> followed by an exclamation mark (<emphasis>!</"
"emphasis>) and an <emphasis>identifier</emphasis>, which will make the "
"engine first follow the order and then switch to the other context, &eg; "
"<userinput>#pop#pop!OtherContext</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Un <emphasis>ordre</emphasis> suivi par un point d'exclamation (<emphasis>!</"
"emphasis>) et un <emphasis>identificateur</emphasis>fera que le moteur "
"suivra d'abord l'ordre, puis basculera vers l'autre contexte, par exemple "
"<userinput>#pop#pop#!autreContexte</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:684
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An <emphasis>identifier</emphasis>, which is a context name, followed by two "
"hashes (<userinput>##</userinput>) and another <emphasis>identifier</"
"emphasis>, which is the name of a language definition. This naming is "
"similar to that used in <userinput>IncludeRules</userinput> rules and allows "
"you to switch to a context belonging to another syntax highlighting "
"definition, e.g. <userinput>SomeContext##JavaScript</userinput>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:694
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Rule specific attributes varies and are described in the following sections."
msgstr ""
"Les attributs spécifiques à une règle varient et sont décrits dans les "
"sections suivantes."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:698
#, no-c-format
msgid "Common attributes"
msgstr "Attributs communs"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:699
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "All rules have the following attributes in common and are available "
#| "whenever <userinput>(common attributes)</userinput> appears. "
#| "<emphasis>attribute</emphasis> and <emphasis>context</emphasis> are "
#| "required attributes, all others are optional."
msgid ""
"All rules have the following attributes in common and are available whenever "
"<userinput>(common attributes)</userinput> appears. All attributes are "
"optional."
msgstr ""
"Toutes les règles ont les attributs suivants en commun et sont disponibles "
"chaque fois que <userinput>(common attributes)</userinput> apparaît. "
"<emphasis>attribute</emphasis> et <emphasis>context</emphasis> sont des "
"attributs requis, tous les autres sont optionnels."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:705
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<emphasis>attribute</emphasis>: An attribute maps to a defined "
#| "<emphasis>itemData</emphasis>."
msgid ""
"<emphasis>attribute</emphasis>: An attribute maps to a defined "
"<emphasis>itemData</emphasis>. Default: <emphasis>attribute</emphasis> from "
"the context specified in <emphasis>context</emphasis> attribute."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>attribute</emphasis> : un attribut établit une correspondance vers "
"un <emphasis>itemData</emphasis> défini."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:708
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<emphasis>context</emphasis>: Specify the context to which the "
#| "highlighting system switches if the rule matches."
msgid ""
"<emphasis>context</emphasis>: Specify the context to which the highlighting "
"system switches if the rule matches. Default: #stay."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>context</emphasis> : spécifie le contexte vers lequel le système "
"de coloration syntaxique bascule si la règle correspond."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:711
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>beginRegion</emphasis>: Start a code folding block. Default: unset."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>beginRegion</emphasis> : démarre un bloc de pliage de code. Par "
"défaut : unset."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>endRegion</emphasis>: Close a code folding block. Default: unset."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>endRegion</emphasis> : ferme un bloc de pliage de code. Par "
"défaut : unset."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:717
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>lookAhead</emphasis>: If <emphasis>true</emphasis>, the "
"highlighting system will not process the matches length. Default: "
"<emphasis>false</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>lookAhead</emphasis> : si <emphasis>true</emphasis>, le système de "
"coloration syntaxique ne traitera pas la longueur des correspondances. Par "
"défaut : <emphasis> false</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:722
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>firstNonSpace</emphasis>: Match only, if the string is the first "
